vices</h3><p>All information, materials and other content („Content“) and all Services provided on the Website, in mailing lists or in webinars (collectively, “the Website”) are free of charge.</p><p>You do not need a user account to use the Website. All Content can be viewed without registration and Submissions can be made anonymously as a guest user. Only when subscribing to a mailing list it is necessary to provide your email adress.</p><p>We reserve the right to change or remove Content or Services, to limit the functionality of Website or to discontinue the Website any time and for any reason.</p><h3>2. User Account</h3><p>You do not need a user account to use the website. All Content can be viewed without registration and Submissions can be made anonymously as a guest user.</p><p>If you register, you have to provide the following information:</p><ul><li>user name</li><li>email address</li><li>avatar (optional)</li><li>password</li></ul><p>You need not provide your actual name. You may use a user name of your own choice so that third parties cannot determine your identity.</p><p>Only your user name and avatar (if any) name will be displayed together with all Submissions that you post to the Website. We will never make your email address public and use it only to communicate with you, e g to provide you with the possibility to reset your password or to subscribe to a mailing list.</p><h3>3. Submissions by users</h3><p>You may post comments, messages on message boards or in webinars or other content such as photographs or videos („Submissions“).</p><p>You may not post Submissions which are obscene, invasive of privacy, abusive, harassing, hateful, infringing of intellectual property rights or otherwise illegal, which encourage such activity or which are otherwise injurious to third parties or objectionable. Objectionable Submissions include Submissions impersonating another person, commercial communication, „flooding“ message boards with unrelated or repeated messages and any other form of „spam“.</p><p>We reserve the right to review submissions and remove, without prior notice, any Submissions which do not comply with the Terms of Use.</p><p>We do not generally monitor Submissions, but we will always review anonymous Submissions before publishing them on the Website.</p><h3>4. Intellectual property</h3><h4>4.1 Our Content</h4><p>All Content published by us is copyrighted property or copyrighted property of our licensors, unless explicitly specified otherwise.</p><p>Subject to your compliance with these Terms of Use, we grant you a non-exclusive licence to view the content and make copies for private use, i e for your personal and non-commercial purposes. Unless specified otherwise or where we grant an explicit additional licence, you may not reproduce, distribute, transmit or otherwise exploit Content for any commercial or non-commercial purpose.</p><p>Even where a licence to reproduce and distribute or transmit Content was granted, you may never (i) remove or alter copyright notices or other proprietary information, (ii) modify Content or use Content to create derivative works, (iii) utilise techniques like framing and embedding without clearly stating the source of the Content.</p><h4>4.2 Submissions by users</h4><p>If you post a Submission, you grant us a non-exclusive, royalty-free, perpetual and fully sublicensable right to reproduce, distribute, transmit and otherwise exploit your Submission, in particular by making it availavle to the public on the Website.</p><p>You represent that you own or control all the rights to Submissions that you post.</p><h3>5. Prohibited use of the Website and sanctions</h3><p>You may not use the website employing software or other tools to enable automated use of the website or to gather or extract Content, e g crawling Content or using bots to post Submissions.</p><p>You may not use the Website in a way that is intended or likely to affect the functionality of the Website.</p><p>You may